2393472368_209280356_1	http://mp.weixin.qq.com/s?__biz=MjM5MzQ3MjM2OA==&mid=209280356&idx=1&sn=dc5dc5e922c9d486c9debc4b550455f6#rd	天天吗哪-【从根本上做对】	 　 　《以弗所书》2:10-22　 　钥节：并且被建造在使徒和先知的根基上，有基督耶稣自己为房角石 (《以弗所书》2:20)　 　古时候建造一栋能长久保存的建筑的结构力学，要求建造者为打地基预备一块基准石。这块石头放在最边缘的角落，用来设定牢固地基的界限。房角石的角度需要极其精准，因为它将决定之后建造的建筑物的线条和角度，在整个建造工程中是横梁、墙壁走向的标准。换句话说，房子的牢固性和耐久性都取决于那一块房角石，现在被称为奠基石。　 　这正是神今天教导基督徒的功课：耶稣基督是从底部加固结构中最初的、也是最重要的那部分，教会其他的一切都是以基督为标准。我们在教会所教导的必须与主耶稣基督的教训一致。我们一定要关注失丧世人永恒的属灵福利，也要顾及神百姓的充分发展和全备成长。　 　耶稣是教会根基的房角石，凡建造的都要殷勤地定睛于k。这样才能在基督徒的跑道上跑对，“因为离了我（耶稣基督），你们就不能作什么”（参《约翰福音》15:5）。　 　所以初期教会遇到外邦寡妇在食物管理上不满的时候，领袖忌邪地抵制一切干扰神纯净话语教导的因素（《使徒行传》6:1-7）。学习并忠心地遵守耶稣基督的教义应该是教会一切活动的中心，其余的都是次要的。建造房屋的每一部分都是次要的，都得根据结构选好房角石。这才是基督徒必须坚持的。　 　今日思想：站在万古磐石上，你就不会被时代的危机震动。　 　 　 　GETTING IT RIGHT FROM THE ROOT     TEXT: EPHESIANS 2:10-22　 　KEY VERSE: “And are built upon the foundation of the apostles and prophets, Jesus Christ himself being the chief corner stone” (Ephesians 2:20).　 　The dynamics of erecting an enduring structure in ancient times required a start with what builders called an alignment stone for the foundation. The stone lay at an extreme corner to set the parameters for a strong base. This angle of the cornerstone was very precise, determining all of the subsequent lines and other angles of the building. It became a standard for the bearing of the beams and walls in the construction of the whole work. In other words, the strength and durability of the building derived from the alignment stone known in modern times as the cornerstone.　 　That exactly is what God is teaching believers in today’s study: Jesus Christ is the First and Foremost component of the undergirding structure upon which everything else in the Church is aligned. Whatever we teach in the church must line up with the doctrine of our Lord Jesus Christ. We must have concern for the eternal welfare of a spiritually lost world, as well as for the development of God’s people to full and perfect growth.　 　Jesus is the Cornerstone of the foundation of the Church, and those who would build upon that foundation must be diligent to keep their eyes on Him. That is the way to get it right in the Christian race, since “without me (Jesus Christ) ye can do nothing” (John 15:5).　 　This is the reason why the leaders of the early Church jealously guarded against distraction from the teaching of the sound word of God when there was discontent over food administration to the Gentile widows (Acts 6:1-7). Studying and abiding faithfully with the doctrine of Jesus Christ should form the center-piece of all activities in the church. All else should be secondary; the same way every element of a building is secondary and dependent on the cornerstone of the structure. Only that way can the believer abide.　 　THOUGHT FOR THE DAY: Stand on the Rock of Ages, and you won’t be rocked by the crisis of ages.　 　ASTAL C 圣经?真理?生命　 　请添加微信号：ASTAL_PRCC　 　或扫描ASTAL公众平台二维码　 　衷心感谢和祝福您　 　在您的朋友圈中传递祝福吧！　 　报福音传喜信的人，　 　他们的脚踪何等佳美！　 　	0.0	1
